.Dd November 22, 1997
.Os
.Dt CINFO 1
.Sh NAME
.Nm cinfo
.Nd C programming language documentation tool
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm cinfo
.Op Fl cdhlpsV
.Op Fl o Ar file
.Op Fl L Ar dir
.Ar symbol ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm cinfo
utility searchs in his database the user specified
.Ar symbol
and prints the proper
documentation.
.Pp
The options are as follows:
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl c
Ignore case distinctions.
.It Fl d
Turn debug mode on.
.It Fl h
Output in HTML format.
.It Fl l
List symbol paths only, do not output symbol variables.
.It Fl o
Set the output destination to
.Ar file .
.It Fl p
Perform a pattern match string comparison.
.It Fl s
Perform a literal string comparison. This is the default.
.It Fl L
Force
.Nm cinfo
to search into the
.Ar dir
directory.
.It Fl V
Print version information on standard output then exit.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Bl -tag -width CINFODBDIR
.It Ev CINFODBDIR
The environment variable
.Ev CINFODBDIR
is used to determine the
.Nm cinfo
database location.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width @ETCDIR@/*.cinfo.db -compact
.It Pa $CINFODBDIR/*.cinfo.db
cinfo database files
.It Pa @ETCDIR@/*.cinfo.db
cinfo database files
.El
.Sh NOTES
`gzip' compressed databases are supported as well.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr cinfoc 1 ,
.Xr cinfodc 1 ,
.Xr cinfodb 5
